soviets to our proposals yesterday has been positive so now the 
goal is to get moving and try to work out these agreements 
white house press secretary marlin fitzwater called 
shevardnadzes statements a very constructive response our 
ultimate objective is total elimination of chemical weapons and it 
appears that both nations are now ready to act 
bushs proposal is intended to spur a 40nation conference in 
geneva to ban all chemical weapons within 10 years 
the soviets would have to scrap more poison gas as us 
officials contend moscow has far greater stockpiles than washington 
an acknowledged 50000 tons compared to an estimated 30000 tons 
for the united states 
bush proposed a ussoviet agreement to begin those cuts at 
once while an international treaty is worked out in which the 
united states would destroy 98 percent of its chemical weapons over 
eight years if the soviets joined the ban 
the remaining 2 percent would be destroyed within 10 years if 
all nations capable of building such weapons agreed to a total ban 
speaking to delegates of 159 nations on tuesday shevardnadze 
also said moscow is ready to reinstate its moratorium on all 
nuclear explosions any day and hour if the united states 
reciprocates 
he said moscow was considering extending the 1963 nuclear test 
ban treaty to cover underground nuclear explosions 
in another disarmament proposal shevardnadze said that if 
nato countries agree to start talks on tactical shortrange 
nuclear weapons the ussr will respond by further unilateral cuts 
in its tactical nuclear weapons in europe 
he also proposed that the production of nuclear fissionable 
material for weapons be halted and that the ban be verified 
the soviet union has announced it is halting the production of 
enriched uranium 
the weekend agreement that bush and soviet president mikhail s 
gorbachev will hold a summit meeting shows that we have moved 
quite far ahead in solving a number of major bilateral and 
international problems shevardnadze said 
in our view by the time the summit is held next year in late 
spring or early summer we may have passed the last turn on the 
road toward a treaty reducing strategic offensive arms or 
longrange nuclear missiles by 50 percent 
in a speech that praised the right of a people to choose its 
government and course of development shevardnadze also wished 
every success to polands new government the first east bloc 
government not led by communists 
he pledged to cooperate with it 
shevardnadze denounced the socalled movements that allow 
actions humiliating other nations or use terrorist barbaric and 
inhuman methods in waging their struggle a pointed reference to 
kidnappings by shiite moslem extremists in lebanon and palestinian 
guerrilla attacks on israel 
