parliament on wednesday adopted a law 
giving people the right to express opinions or advocate political 
and social change further expanding freedom of speech before 
multiparty elections next year 
the bill and a related amendment of the criminal procedure law 
are part of a package of legislation designed to bring hungarys 
laws in line with moves toward a pluralistic system and with 
international covenants on human rights 
under the penal code amendment which takes effect immediately 
expressing ones private opinion or advocating political or social 
change can no longer be considered crimes 
hungarys rapid liberalization has allowed a degree of free 
expression that would have been difficult even one year ago 
opposition leaders can have their say in the official media and in 
most cases people are permitted to demonstrate freely on a wide 
range of issues including such sensitive topics as the withdrawal 
of soviet troops 
the draft legislation before parliament must create the legal 
preconditions for the transition leading to a new constitutional 
order and eliminate obstacles in the path of the transformation 
to a multiparty system justice minister kalman kulcsar said 
the penal code amendment was designed only to deal with urgent 
matters and a comprehensive penal code reform is under way 
kulcsar said 
jozsef debreczeni one of four new members of parliament who 
belong to the opposition and received the majority vote in recent 
byelections the first in which hungarians had a genuine choice 
