also admitted filing a false tax return in 1987 
both men admitted that from march 1985 to february 1989 fd 
roberts hired brokers with little or no experience and trained them 
to badger customers into buying securities at inflated prices 
kanoff a member of the firms board who shared in its profits 
also told the judge that fd roberts funds were used to pay 
organized crime figures who had undisclosed interests in the firm 
there was money owed to organized crime figures and money to 
be paid to organized crime figures said first assistant us 
attorney michael chertoff 
kanoff faces 15 years in prison and fines of up to 750000 
weiss faces a 13year prison term and fines of up to 750000 
sentencing was set for november 14 
kanoff weiss and the three others who entered guilty pleas told 
the judge that fd roberts brokers used deceptive and manipulative 
sales techniques to persuade customers to buy stocks the firm 
usually controlled and that false records were maintained 
they also said some of those involved in fraudulent activity 
would would maintain nominee accounts and profit by as much as 400 
percent in one day 
earlier wednesday three former brokers john landrum 31 and 
kevin zacharawicz 35 both of boca raton fla and fred schneider 
of sparta pleaded guilty to stock fraud 
each faces a fiveyear jail term and a 250000 fine 
fd roberts had branch offices in new york florida and 
california 
penny stocks are lowpriced securities that are not listed on 
any exchange 
the firm which has been under investigation by state and 
federal authorities for about 1years voluntarily closed in 
february after the national association of securities dealers 
informed it that it fell below the minimum capital requirements 
fd roberts former national sales manager a former branch 
manager two assistant branch managers and two other brokers 
already have pleaded guilty to using similar fraudulent practices 
on clients 
four of the firms top executives including kanoff have been 
banned by the nasd from working in the securities industry 
</TEXT>
